  <a href="#0" id="0">
   Unsupervised domain adaptation often relies on transforming the instance representation.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   However, most such approaches are designed for bag-of-words models, and ignore the structured features present in many problems in NLP.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   We propose a new technique called marginalized structured dropout , which exploits feature structure to obtain a remarkably simple and efficient feature projection.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Applied to the task of fine-grained part-of-speech tagging on a dataset of historical Portuguese, marginalized structured dropout yields state-of-the-art accuracy while increasing speed by more than an order-of-magnitude over previous work.
  </a>
